snippet: Hanyu’s free skate at the Cup of China in Shanghai began with a scary crash with another skater in warm-ups, but he decided to stay in the competition and nearly won the title anyway.
abstract: Yuzuru Hanyu’s nearly wins free skate at Cup of China in Shanghai despite fairly serious crash with another skater in warm-ups; Maxim Kovtun of Russia takes event's gold medal.
lead_paragraph: Hanyu’s free skate at the Cup of China in Shanghai began with a scary crash with another skater in warm-ups, but he decided to stay in the competition and nearly won the title anyway.

headline.main: Yuzuru Hanyu Nearly Wins Despite Collision
